President Obama has announced his intent to appoint Sondra Myers and Jackie Norris to key administration posts. Sondra Myers is currently a Senior Fellow at the University of Scranton and the Director of its Schemel Forum. She has also served in various roles such as Special Assistant to the Chairman for Partnerships at the National Endowment for the Humanities and Cultural Advisor to Pennsylvania Governor Robert P. Casey. Jackie Norris is the Executive Director of the Points of Light Corporate Institute and an Adjunct Professor at American University's School of Public Affairs. She previously served as Senior Advisor to the CEO of the Corporation for National and Community Service and as Assistant to the President and Chief of Staff to the First Lady. Norris also worked as a high school government teacher in Iowa and is a recipient of the James Madison Fellowship.